flowRoot.flowPara: NLTK[0] is a leading platform for building Python programs to work with human language data.
The setting: A few thousand emails were sent to a school district in the summer of 2012 following an incident involving some of their students.
The task: Analyze the text for positive or negative sentiment, key words, patterns.
* Data started life as an Access database
* Many emails pointed to youtube videos of the incident, which confuse NLTK
These tagged tokens can be run through any number of NLTK functions to extract meaning
NLTK includes classifiers and other learning algorithms to make sense of your data
NLTK[0] is a library for parsing and understanding natural language with Python.

The first step is to take a block of text and split it into atomic tokens of words. These tokens may then be analyzed for which part of speech they belong to. This produces a list of tuples containing (token, tag)
Tokenizing: Taking a string of words and splitting them into individual words or tokens.
Tagging: Taking a token in the context of the sentence to find the part of speech it is (verb, noun, preposition, etc.)
Stemming: Taking the stem, or root of a word by cutting the end off until a common prefix is found.
Lemmatization: Taking known different forms of a word and treating them as the same word.
Classification: A process of training and applying a set of rules to a dataset so that a decision may be reached about their content.
Using natural language parsing to extract meaning from large quantities of text
